 <center> 
  <h1><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The Execution Model</font></h1> 
 </center> 
 
<p><br>
  <font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Execution Model</font></p>
<ul>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">The execution model is the a description 
    of how the adaptation model picks the adaptation rules and executes them</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Like the Adaption Engine, the 
    Execution Model does not appear in the AHAM Model diagram because it is not 
    conceptual</font></li>
</ul>
<p><font size="4" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Adaptation Rule Execution 
  Phases</font></p>
<ul>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">IU - Initialize User Model Phase 
    (The Domain Model and User Model are loaded)</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">PS - Page Selection Phase</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">UU - Update User Model Phase</font></li>
  <li><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">GA - Generate Adaptation Phase</font></li>
</ul>
<p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Each phase represented above is accomplished 
  by the execution of some adaptation rules. Grouping of the rules, and enforcement 
  of the sequence of each phases rules can be achieved with the use of a priority 
  scheme. UI rules have the highest priority rules.</font></p>
</html> 
